&lt;pre&gt;Hey Ashley,

I suspect the M133 in the chrome status page will be updated to a later
release. I also put the bug link (&lt;a  rel="nofollow" href="https://issues.chromium.org/40277080"&gt;https://issues.chromium.org/40277080&lt;/a&gt;) on
that page.&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;pre&gt;

Thanks for the feedback. Right now we're in a situation where we definitely
need to remove SwiftShader WebGL support but we're evaluating other ways to
support fallback based on this kind of thread. WARP is a possibility but
still suffers from continuing to run JITed code in processes that are high
security risk and difficult to sandbox.

The &quot;users have a poor experience&quot; situation is more than just content
running slowly. A common case where users result in software fallback is
due to GPU driver crashes and hangs, to the user this is a series of
flickers and hangs in the page followed by it running slowly because the
whole browser switched to software rendering.

We'll likely update the feature page again once David is back from holiday.

Geoff



