&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; were significantly worse for the deprecation of the old `shadowroot`
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; attribute, and the removal of that feature generated zero bug reports. 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; It
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; is my strong belief that since this feature is only shipped in Chrome, 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; the
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; vast majority of usage is guarded by feature checks. So this 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; deprecation
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; should be safer than it would seem from the numbers. I'd like to remove
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; this feature in M127 in code, with a killswitch (a re-enable switch 
&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt;&gt; really)
